copy.general_description:
The 2022 DPC South America Tour 2 is also a part of the (Dota Pro Circuit) tournament organized by 4D Esports; This tournament will also serve as a qualifying tournament in preparation for the biggest DOTA2 event, The International.

The tournament will feature both notable and the best teams from Europe, China, Southeast Asia, North America, and South America, with a prize pool for each region amounting to $205,000 for Upper Division and $75,000 for the Lower Division.

The points acquired from this tournament will determine their qualification for the Major Event and eventually The International 2022.
copy.short_description: The 2022 DPC South America Tour 2 is also a part of the (Dota Pro Circuit) tournament organized by 4D Esports.
copy.format_description:
Group Stage will be played in a round-robin best-of-three series.

The top two teams will be seeded to Division 1 for the next tour and the bottom two teams will be eliminated; the remaining teams will remain their spot in their current division for the next tour.

tournament.title: Claro Gaming Apu League Sunset Series

copy.general_description: From the successful third Season of Claro Gaming, PESA will have another blast this 2022 with the Sunset Series of Claro Gaming Apu League. Claro, Monster, and Adidas will sponsor this tournament featuring eight teams from the South American region battling for the crown and the prize pool of $5,093.
copy.short_description: Claro Gaming Apu League Season 3 is an online tournament from South America with a prize pool of $5,093.
copy.format_description:
The main event will start with a group stage and proceed with playoffs.

Group stage will be played in two groups of four teams in GSL format. all matches are best-of-three top two teams from each group advance to the playoffs. The bottom two teams from each group are eliminated.

Playoffs will be played in a Double Elimination bracket all matches are best-of-three except Grand Finals which is a best-of-five series.

copy.general_description: Following the success of the BTS Pro Series, the 10th season is an esports tournament focused on creating unique and authentic events featuring the best teams that will represent their region
copy.short_description: Following the success of the BTS Pro Series, the 10th season is an esports tournament featuring the best teams that will represent their region
copy.format_description:
Twelve invited teams, eight teams are seeded into Phase 1 and five teams are seeded into Phase 2.

Phase 1 will be played in a double-elimination bracket format and all matches are best-of-three top four teams will qualify to Phase 2.

Phase 2 will be played in a single round-robin and all matches are best-of-two, top four teams advance to the upper bracket Phase 3, the 5th to 8th place team is eliminated.

Phase 3 will be played in a double-elimination bracket format and all matches are best-of-three except the Grand Final which is best-of-five.

copy.general_description:
The 2021 Elisa Invitational tournament is now on its Winter edition, featuring teams from the Nordic region together with some notable teams in the world who will clash and fight for the $100,000 prize pool.

The tournament will be running from the 8th of November through the 5th of March lets find out who will be hail as the year-ending tournament champion of the Elisa Invitational
copy.short_description: The 2021 Elisa Invitational tournament is now on its Winter edition, featuring teams from the Nordic region and a $100,000 prize pool at stake.
copy.format_description:
The tournament will begin with regional qualifiers from these three Nordic regions (Finland, Norway, and Sweden) and will be playing in the single-elimination best-of-three series, the winners of each region will proceed in the Online Stage of the main event.

Online Stage is composed of Sixteen teams where only the top eight teams of this group will proceed to the final stage, all matches are played in round-robin best-of-three series.

Online Playoffs will be played in single-elimination best-of-three series and the top 4 teams will advance and play for the LAN finals.

The group stage of the main event will be played in GSL format composed of two groups of four, each group's initial matches and winner's matches are played in the best-of-one series while elimination and decider matches are played in the best-of-three series.

Playoffs will be played in single-elimination best-of-three series.
